essional-grade stainless steel blades stay sharp\n- Safety stop prevents overcutting\n- Ergonomic, non-slip grip handles\n- Suitable for small to medium parrots\n- Can be used on both nails and minor beak corrections\n\n**Cons:**\n- Requires practice and confidence to use safely\n- Not suitable for large birds like Macaws without extra care\n- Blade dulls over time and needs sharpening\n- Risk of splintering if nails are cut too close to the quick\n\n---\n\n## Best Nail Care Tools\n\n### 4. Safari Nail Trimmer for Birds\n\nThe Safari Nail Trimmer is a guillotine-style clipper specifically engineered for bird nails. The stainless steel blade delivers a clean cut on the first try, reducing the chance of nail splintering. The plastic guard helps control cutting depth, making it ideal for first-time bird groomers.\n\n- **Price:** ~$9鈥?14\n- **ASIN:** B0002H3L1C\n- **Link:** https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0002H3L1C?tag=paw070-20\n\n**Pros:**\n- Affordable and widely available\n- Built-in safety guard reduces risk of cutting the quick\n- Sharp stainless steel blade for clean cuts\n- Lightweight and easy to maneuver\n- Good for small to medium birds\n\n**Cons:**\n- Plastic guard can break with heavy use\n- Not ideal for very large birds with thick nails\n- Blade may dull after repeated use\n- Requires firm hold to avoid nail splintering\n\n---\n\n### 5. KAKEI Bird Nail Clipper Professional Small Pet\n\nThe KAKEI Professional Bird Nail Clipper is a scissor-style trimmer designed for precision on small and medium parrots. The curved blade follows the natural shape of the nail, helping prevent splitting. A locking mechanism keeps the blades safely closed when not in use, and the handles are rubber-coated for a comfortable, secure grip.\n\n- **Price:** ~$16鈥?20\n- **ASIN:** B07D4QZ3X1\n- **Link:** https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07D4QZ3X1?tag=paw070-20\n\n**Pros:**\n- Curved blade follows nail anatomy for cleaner cuts\n- Rubber-coated handles for non-slip grip\n- Locking mechanism for 